# Bench Press Activator — Leader Dashboard

A lightweight, static dashboard that lets leaders at a digital agency view their team members grouped by survey-assigned persona (from the "Activator" framework). Built as a zero-dependency prototype — no build tools, no frameworks, just HTML + CSS + vanilla JS.

---

## What It Does

- Displays a **leader profile card** (name, role, market)
- Shows a **sortable team table** with columns: Name, Title, Market, Dominant Persona, Secondary Persona, Client Facing
- Each team member has a **dominant persona** and a **secondary persona** (Confidant, Activator, Realist, Debater, Expert)
- Each member gets a **composite "client-facing" persona** (e.g. "Trusted Advisor", "Bold Instigator") derived from their dominant + secondary combination — 20 possible composites
- Multiple team members can share the same composite persona
- Click any **row** to open a **member detail modal** showing:
  - Composite persona hero section with code badge (e.g. Ce, Ad) and blend name
  - SVG radar chart visualizing scores across all 5 persona dimensions
  - Persona profile bar chart (percentage breakdown across all 5 personas, totaling 100%)
  - Dominant persona interpretation (identity, signals, risk, leadership takeaway, client impression)
  - Suggested pairings — complementary teammates with rationale
- **Persona reference section** below the table with:
  - Introductory text explaining the core/wing/balance-point model
  - Interactive persona model diagram
  - 5 persona cards with descriptions
  - Persona description modal on card click

---

## Composite Persona System

Every team member's dominant + secondary persona produces one of 20 composite personas, each with a unique name, description, and color-coded badge. Composites are grouped by primary persona family:

| Primary | Composites |
|---------|-----------|
| Confidant | The Connector (Ca), The Anchor (Cr), Trusted Challenger (Cd), Trusted Advisor (Ce) |
| Activator | The Rainmaker (Ac), Disciplined Driver (Ar), Bold Instigator (Ad), Credible Catalyst (Ae) |
| Realist | Honest Broker (Rc), Pragmatic Driver (Ra), Straight Shooter (Rd), The Validator (Re) |
| Debater | Diplomatic Challenger (Dc), The Disruptor (Da), Devil's Advocate (Dr), Thought Leader (De) |
| Expert | Go-To Specialist (Ec), The Evangelist (Ea), The Craftsman (Er), The Visionary (Ed) |

Each composite badge has a unique color within its primary persona's color family (blues, corals, cyans, purples, navies).

---

## The Survey Model

The app simulates results from a 25-question behavioral assessment:
- Each question has 5 answer choices, one per persona (A=Activator, B=Expert, C=Confidant, D=Debater, E=Realist)
- Scoring: count answers per persona ÷ 25 × 100 = percentage
- Result is a profile that sums to 100%, revealing dominant tendencies

---

## File Structure

```
├── index.html          # App shell — header, table, persona reference, two modals
├── app.js              # All logic: data, sorting, modal rendering, composite system, radar chart
├── styles.css          # Full styling (Bench Press design system tokens, 20 composite colors)
├── styleguide.md       # Design system reference (from Hackathon Hub)
├── BRIEF.md            # Original product brief / requirements
└── README              # This file
```

---

## Running Locally

No install needed. Open `index.html` in a browser:

```bash
# macOS / Linux
open index.html

# Windows
start index.html

# Or use VS Code Live Server, Python http.server, etc.
python -m http.server 8000
```

---

## Key Architecture Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| Static HTML (no framework) | Fast prototyping, zero build step, easy to share |
| Data hardcoded in `app.js` | Swap the `teamMembers` array for an API call when ready |
| 20 composite colors via `data-composite` | CSS handles all color mapping — each composite code (Ca, Cr, etc.) gets a unique badge color |
| Survey results as % profile (sum to 100%) | Matches the real 25-question scoring model from the Activator framework |
| Composite persona system | Dominant + secondary → one of 20 named composites with unique identity and color |
| SVG radar chart in modal | Visualizes persona profile without any charting library |
| Pairing logic in JS | Complementary persona mapping lives in `pairingRationale` — easy to tune |
| CSS custom properties (design tokens) | All colors, radii, shadows, fonts defined in `:root` for easy theming |
| Fixed table layout | Prevents column-width jumping when sorting |

---

## Porting Guide

### Connecting to Real Data

Replace the `teamMembers` array at the top of `app.js` with a fetch call. Expected shape per member:

```js
{
  name: "string",
  title: "string",
  market: "string",
  persona: "Confidant" | "Activator" | "Realist" | "Debater" | "Expert",
  secondaryPersona: "Confidant" | "Activator" | "Realist" | "Debater" | "Expert",
  // Derived at runtime:
  // clientFacing: "Trusted Advisor"  (composite name from blendedPersonas)
  // compositeCode: "Ce"             (primary initial + lowercase secondary initial)
  surveyResults: {          // optional — generated if missing
    Activator: number,      // percentage (all five sum to 100)
    Expert: number,
    Confidant: number,
    Debater: number,
    Realist: number,
  }
}
```

### Adding / Changing Personas

1. Add the new persona name to the `personas` array in `app.js`
2. Add a color entry to `personaColors` in `app.js`
3. Add a description entry to `personaDescriptions` in `app.js`
4. Add composite entries to `blendedPersonas` for all pairings with the new persona
5. Add a CSS rule: `.persona-badge[data-persona="NewName"] { background: #HEX; }`
6. Add CSS rules for each new composite: `.client-facing-badge[data-composite="Xn"] { ... }`
7. Add pairing rationale in `pairingRationale`

### Changing the Leader Profile

Edit the hardcoded HTML in `index.html` (`.leader-profile` section), or pull from an API.

### Adapting the Style

The app uses the Bench Press design system (sourced from Hackathon Hub). Key tokens:
- **Primary blue:** `#0C62FB`
- **Dark slate (header/text):** `#0F172A`
- **Fonts:** Nunito Sans (primary), Lora (serif accent), DM Mono (data)
- **Border radius:** Asymmetric "Slalom cut" — top-right only (e.g. `0 24px 0 0`)
- **Persona colors:** blue, coral, cyan, purple, dark blue

All tokens are CSS custom properties in `:root` — see `styleguide.md` for the full reference.

### Deploying

Since it's fully static, deploy anywhere:
- **GitHub Pages** — push and enable in repo settings
- **Vercel / Netlify** — drop the folder, no config needed
- **SharePoint** — upload as a static site

---

## Dependencies

| Dependency | Source | Purpose |
|------------|--------|---------|
| Nunito Sans, Lora, DM Mono | Google Fonts (via CSS `@import`) | Typography |
| Material Symbols Outlined | Google Fonts CDN | Icons (person, close) |

No npm packages. No build step. No runtime dependencies.